cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper deals with texture synthesis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of a generative adversarial network (GAN) is a popular technique in deep learning (cs.LG) and the paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for texture synthesis, which is another common topic in deep learning. The paper also mentions the use of texture blocks, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach for non-stationary texture synthesis, which involves learning from a specific texture exemplar, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
